class Stack:
    def __init__(self, array = None):
        super().__init__()
        self.array = array

    # 
    def push(self, x):
        self.array.append(x)

    # 
    def pop(self,):
        if len(self.array) == 0:
            return

        return self.array.pop()

    # 
    def top(self,):
        if len(self.array) == 0:
            return

        return self.array[-1]

    # 
    def isEmpty(self,):
        return True if self.array == [] else False


class Queue:
    def __init__(self, array = None):
        super().__init__()
        self.array = array

    # 
    def enqueue(self, x):
        self.array.append(x)

    # 
    def dequeue(self):
        if len(self.array) == 0:
            return

        return self.array.pop(0)

    # 
    def isEmpty(self,):
        return True if self.array == [] else False
